  "local_port": 60154,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "Using WhatsApp on a PC is a convenient way to stay connected while working on your computer. You can access WhatsApp on your desktop through **WhatsApp Web** or by downloading the **WhatsApp Desktop** application. Below are detailed instructions on how to set up and use WhatsApp on your PC.\n\n---\n\n## Method 1: Using WhatsApp Web\n\n**WhatsApp Web** allows you to access your WhatsApp account directly from your browser. Here's how to set it up:\n\n### Step 1: Open Your Web Browser\n\n1. Launch your preferred web browser (e.g., Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Microsoft Edge, Safari).\n2. Navigate to [WhatsApp Web](https://web.whatsapp.com).\n\n### Step 2: Open WhatsApp on Your Smartphone\n\n- **For Android Users:**\n  1. Open the **WhatsApp** app.\n  2. Tap the **three-dot menu icon** in the top-right corner.\n  3. Select **Linked Devices**.\n  4. Tap **Link a device**.\n\n- **For iPhone Users:**\n  1. Open the **WhatsApp** app.\n  2. Tap **Settings** at the bottom right.\n  3. Select **Linked Devices**.\n  4. Tap **Link a Device**.\n\n### Step 3: Scan the QR Code\n\n1. On your PC screen, you'll see a **QR code** from WhatsApp Web.\n2. On your smartphone, use the WhatsApp app to scan the QR code:\n   - Position your phone's camera over the QR code on your PC screen until it's recognized.\n3. Once scanned, your WhatsApp account will be mirrored on your browser.\n\n### Step 4: Start Using WhatsApp on Your PC\n\n- You can now send and receive messages, view media, manage your chats, and perform most activities available on the mobile app directly from your browser.\n\n---\n\n## Method 2: Using WhatsApp Desktop Application\n\nIf you prefer a standalone application instead of using a browser, you can download the WhatsApp Desktop app.\n\n### Step 1: Download WhatsApp Desktop\n\n1. Visit the [WhatsApp Download Page](https://www.whatsapp.com/download) from your PC.\n2. Click on the **Download for Windows** or **Download for Mac OS X** button, depending on your operating system.\n3. Alternatively, you can go to the Microsoft Store (for Windows) or the Mac App Store (for macOS) and search for **WhatsApp Desktop** to download and install.\n\n### Step 2: Install the Application\n\n1. Once the download is complete, open the installer.\n2. Follow the on-screen instructions to install WhatsApp Desktop on your computer.\n\n### Step 3: Open WhatsApp Desktop and Link Your Device\n\n1. Launch the **WhatsApp Desktop** application.\n2. You will see a QR code on the application window.\n3. On your smartphone, open WhatsApp and follow these steps:\n   - **For Android:** Tap the **three-dot menu icon** > **Linked Devices** > **Link a device**.\n   - **For iPhone:** Tap **Settings** > **Linked Devices** > **Link a Device**.\n4. Use your phone to scan the QR code displayed on the desktop application.\n5. Once scanned, your WhatsApp account will sync with the desktop app.\n\n### Step 4: Start Using WhatsApp on Your PC\n\n- You can now interact with your WhatsApp contacts, send messages, share files, and use most features available on the mobile app within the desktop application.\n\n---\n\n## Important Notes\n\n- **Internet Connection:** Both your smartphone and PC need to be connected to the internet for WhatsApp Web or Desktop to work. If your phone loses internet connectivity, WhatsApp on your PC will not function.\n  \n- **Security:** Ensure you are using WhatsApp Web or Desktop on a secure and trusted computer to protect your privacy. Always log out from WhatsApp Web/Desktop when using a public or shared computer.\n  \n  - To log out:\n    - **On WhatsApp Web:** Click on the **three-dot menu icon** at the top of the chat list and select **Log out**.\n    - **On WhatsApp Desktop:** Click on the **three-dot menu icon** or **gear icon**, and choose **Log out**.\n  \n- **Notifications:** You can enable desktop notifications to receive alerts for new messages even when you're not actively using WhatsApp on your PC. To enable:\n  - Click on the **three-dot menu icon** or **settings icon** in WhatsApp Web/Desktop.\n  - Navigate to **Settings** > **Notifications**.\n  - Enable **Desktop Notifications**.\n\n- **Updates:** Make sure to keep the WhatsApp Desktop application updated to access the latest features and security improvements.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nUsing WhatsApp on your PC through WhatsApp Web or the Desktop application enhances your messaging experience by allowing you to type on a physical keyboard and manage your chats alongside other desktop activities. Whether you choose to use the browser-based WhatsApp Web or download the dedicated Desktop app, the setup process is straightforward and quick.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during setup, ensure that both your phone and PC have active internet connections, and check that you're scanning the QR code correctly. For further assistance, you can visit the [WhatsApp Help Center](https://faq.whatsapp.com).\n\n---\n\nFeel free to reach out if you have any more questions or need further assistance!",
